WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Bordo' is a game played on an 8 by 8 tiles board; the center
6 by 6 tiles area is occupied by coloured tiles and the border
tiles on the board have triangular shaped icons that are used to
move coloured tiles. The idea is to align 3 tiles or more of the
same colour on the border tiles of the game board. The tiles may
be placed horizontally, vertically or both.

  When 3 or more tiles of the same colour are lined-up, they are
removed from the board and you get points according to the number
of tiles removed. Any time you move tiles by one position and it
doesn't create 3 matching tiles, a new tile is added on the game
board, if the entire game board gets full, the game is over.

  Have fun!

